{"type":"step-attempt","step":"cross-boundary-invariants","sessionId":"4d0ba0e3-559c-4ce3-b272-520acfb6deeb","outcome":{"verdict":"approved","findingsPath":"specrunner/changes/jobstatestore-internal-split/cross-boundary-invariants-result-001.md","error":null,"toolResult":{"ok":true,"approved":true,"findings":[],"observations":[{"severity":"low","file":"src/store/job-state-projection.ts","title":"type-only import cycle deviates from design DAG claim","rationale":"design.md states the dependency graph is a DAG with no cycle. job-state-projection.ts imports `import type { JournalCounters }` from job-journal.ts, while job-journal.ts imports stateToStateJson from job-state-projection.ts at runtime. The type-only import is erased at compile time so no runtime cycle exists and typecheck passes. However the structural dependency graph deviates from the stated DAG at the type level.","line":11},{"severity":"low","file":"src/store/job-state-projection.ts","title":"stateToStateJson placed in job-state-projection.ts, not job-journal.ts as design.md risk section stated","rationale":"design.md risk section says both stateToStateJson and buildStepCounts move to job-journal.ts. tasks.md T-03 directed stateToStateJson to job-state-projection.ts instead. The implementation follows tasks.md. Behavioral result is identical; the inconsistency is between design prose and tasks only.","line":155},{"severity":"low","file":"src/store/job-state-projection.ts","title":"composeSplitLayout, loadSplitLayout, stateToStateJson are now importable by any code in src/store/","rationale":"These were private module-scope functions in job-state-store.ts. As exported functions in job-state-projection.ts they are accessible to any file that imports directly from that module, bypassing the index.ts boundary. No existing caller does this; the index.ts public surface is unchanged.","line":15}]},"followUpAttempts":1,"transientRetryAttempts":0},"startedAt":"2026-07-13T16:42:44.637Z","endedAt":"2026-07-13T16:48:52.566Z"}
